      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it sounds wild, but i'm not just talking about \"ideas\" here. i actually felt the physical vibration in my chest and the air literally felt heavy immediately after. it wasn't just a feeling, it was like a physical shift in the room's energy. \n\nif we look at it through physics—like acoustic resonance or how standing waves work in a fluid medium—can't you see there's a mathematical way this could work? even if the big machines don't do it yet, what would the theoretical frequency be to create an opposing wave to a pressure drop? just give me the math, i want to see if the numbers actually line up with what i felt.",
      "source": "evaluator"
